# Most Actio configuration lives in `<config.data_dir>/settings.json` and
# is round-tripped through the GUI (Settings → AI / Audio / Models / etc.).
# `PATCH /settings` hot-reloads the running pipeline. The environment
# variables below are bootstrap-only — they seed initial values when the
# app first launches with no settings.json on disk.

# ── Logging ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Standard `tracing` filter. Useful values:
#   RUST_LOG=actio_core=info            (production-ish)
#   RUST_LOG=actio_core=debug,sqlx=warn (debug app, quiet sqlx)
RUST_LOG=actio_core=info

# ── Remote LLM seed (optional) ─────────────────────────────────────────
# If both LLM_BASE_URL and LLM_API_KEY are set when Actio first starts,
# the Remote LLM router is pre-populated with these values. After the
# first launch, the user manages them through Settings → AI; the env
# vars are no longer consulted.
# LLM_BASE_URL=https://api.openai.com/v1
# LLM_API_KEY=sk-...
# LLM_MODEL=gpt-4o-mini   # default: gpt-4o-mini

# ── No DATABASE_URL, no Python worker, no HTTP_PORT ────────────────────
# SQLite path is computed from `<config.data_dir>/actio.db` (data_dir
# defaults to the OS-appropriate per-user location and is overridable
# via the Tauri shell). HTTP server binds to 127.0.0.1:3000 with
# fallback to 3001-3009 (see frontend/src/api/backend-url.ts for the
# discovery probe). There is no Python worker.
